I think it is.

17
00:02:19,931 --> 00:02:21,641
What's your name?
What school do you go to?

18
00:02:22,475 --> 00:02:24,185
Let's talk inside the police station.

19
00:02:26,604 --> 00:02:28,231
I should take you to the hospital first.

20
00:02:28,314 --> 00:02:30,316
Snap out of it.
You need to talk to me so I can help.

21
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:31,359
No, I…

22
00:02:32,777 --> 00:02:34,070
It's not that…

23
00:02:36,990 --> 00:02:40,160
I got it! The roof of building 101!

24
00:02:40,243 --> 00:02:41,494
Send in the task force!

25
00:02:41,578 --> 00:02:43,037
We're on our way!

26
00:02:56,134 --> 00:02:59,304
I killed someone…

27
00:03:03,474 --> 00:03:04,434
What?

28
00:03:08,438 --> 00:03:09,564
…with this.

29
00:03:21,117 --> 00:03:23,119
ABOLISH THE JUVENILE ACT
AND SERVE MURDERERS JUSTICE

30
00:03:23,203 --> 00:03:25,079
RAISE THE LEGAL THRESHOLD
FOR JUVENILE OFFENDERS

31
00:03:25,163 --> 00:03:29,167
The assailant who murdered
and mutilated an eight-year-old

32
00:03:29,250 --> 00:03:33,171
has turned himself in
eight hours after committing the crime.

33
00:03:34,088 --> 00:03:36,758
The culprit, Baek,
turned out to be a 13-year-old

34
00:03:36,841 --> 00:03:40,011
who lived in the same apartment complex
as the victim.

35
00:03:40,094 --> 00:03:43,598
Baek has already
been investigated by the police.

36
00:03:43,681 --> 00:03:46,184
However, being under 14 years of age,

37
00:03:46,267 --> 00:03:49,270
he is not subject
to the same laws as an adult.

38
00:03:49,354 --> 00:03:51,689
There is growing controversy
surrounding his punishment.

39
00:03:51,773 --> 00:03:53,191
You're not even human, you asshole!

40
00:04:05,995 --> 00:04:08,957
There are 3,300 judges in Korea,

41
00:04:09,832 --> 00:04:12,794
but only 20 of them work
in the juvenile court.

42
00:04:12,877 --> 00:04:13,920
COURT

43
00:04:14,003 --> 00:04:19,467
Those 20 judges meet
30,000 young offenders every year.

44
00:04:20,426 --> 00:04:25,556
There are no prosecutors
in juvenile court, only assistants.

45
00:04:25,640 --> 00:04:28,351
The judge questions
the young offenders themselves

46
00:04:28,434 --> 00:04:30,561
to decide the kind of probation
they will be put under.

47
00:04:31,145 --> 00:04:34,190
And that's when their work really starts.

48
00:04:35,566 --> 00:04:39,237
They need to see
if the young offender is adjusting well.

49
00:04:40,196 --> 00:04:44,325
They need to make sure the young offender
doesn't run away or commit another crime.

50
00:04:45,368 --> 00:04:48,329
The judge in charge needs
to constantly manage and supervise them.

51
00:04:48,413 --> 00:04:49,831
That's strange.

52
00:04:49,914 --> 00:04:52,709
Why does the judge do that
when the trial is over?

53
00:04:53,459 --> 00:04:55,670
The purpose of the Juvenile Act is

54
00:04:55,753 --> 00:04:59,090
to provide the proper environment
in which anti-social juveniles

55
00:04:59,590 --> 00:05:01,175
can correct their behavior.

56
00:05:02,135 --> 00:05:07,098
So it's the judge's duty
to manage and supervise them.

57
00:05:07,181 --> 00:05:11,769
So the purpose of juvenile court
isn't to punish them?

58
00:05:13,062 --> 00:05:16,941
Okay, we'll wrap up the interview
after one final question.

59
00:05:17,442 --> 00:05:20,153
Why did you choose
to be a juvenile court judge?

60
00:05:27,827 --> 00:05:29,620
There's only one reason.

61
00:05:31,914 --> 00:05:33,041
Hatred.

62
00:05:34,417 --> 00:05:35,251
Pardon?

63
00:05:38,963 --> 00:05:39,922
I…

64
00:05:41,883 --> 00:05:45,928
detest young offenders.

65
00:06:09,494 --> 00:06:11,704
When will I get feedback on this?

66
00:06:12,747 --> 00:06:14,457
-Is this what you wanted?
-Yes.

67
00:06:14,540 --> 00:06:18,711
Being at a juvenile classification center
doesn't mean he'll have a criminal record.

68
00:06:18,795 --> 00:06:20,046
It's not a prison, ma'am.

69
00:06:20,630 --> 00:06:23,424
Most people think it's a detention center,

70
00:06:23,508 --> 00:06:25,134
but it also counts as school attendance,

71
00:06:25,218 --> 00:06:28,346
and they investigate the case further
and provide therapy…

72
00:06:30,014 --> 00:06:31,015
YEONHWA DISTRICT COURT

73
00:06:31,682 --> 00:06:33,643
Juvenile Criminal Collegiate Division.

74
00:06:34,143 --> 00:06:35,603
What? Which police station?

75
00:06:36,938 --> 00:06:40,858
Yes, hello.
How can I help you this morning?

76
00:06:43,778 --> 00:06:44,987
What?

77
00:06:45,071 --> 00:06:46,322
YEONHWA DISTRICT COURT

78
00:06:57,792 --> 00:06:59,001
JUDGE'S CHAMBERS

79
00:07:04,215 --> 00:07:05,466
Judge Sim Eun-seok?

80
00:07:06,384 --> 00:07:09,804
Hello, I'm Woo Su-mi. I'm a manager here.

81
00:07:10,763 --> 00:07:12,473
You're here earlier than expected.

82
00:07:12,557 --> 00:07:13,683
This way, please.

83
00:07:20,314 --> 00:07:23,734
You were informed that you'll be sharing
the room with another judge, right?

84
00:07:23,818 --> 00:07:26,779
He's a male judge
by the name of Cha Tae-ju.

85
00:07:28,781 --> 00:07:31,075
He spent all night
writing out his rulings.

86
00:07:31,159 --> 00:07:33,744
He just went to go freshen up.

87
00:07:36,998 --> 00:07:37,999
What about Mr. Kang?

88
00:07:39,542 --> 00:07:40,710
Is he inside?

89
00:07:41,711 --> 00:07:42,879
-Great work.
-Thank you.

90
00:07:42,962 --> 00:07:44,464
-Good job.
-Great work.

91
00:07:44,547 --> 00:07:45,673
Thanks.

92
00:07:45,756 --> 00:07:48,384
Next week's shoot
has been postponed a week, right?

93
00:07:48,468 --> 00:07:51,220
Yes. Today's footage should be enough
for the next two weeks.

94
00:07:51,304 --> 00:07:53,973
Gosh, one of the associate judges
quit out of the blue.

95
00:07:54,056 --> 00:07:56,392
We have cases coming in,
but not enough people.

96
00:07:56,476 --> 00:07:57,518
It's driving me crazy.

97
00:07:57,602 --> 00:08:01,856
You're going on air, judging trials,
and even volunteering.

98
00:08:02,690 --> 00:08:03,774
I respect you, Judge Kang.

99
00:08:03,858 --> 00:08:05,401
JUDGE KANG WHO GIVES AND VOLUNTEERS

100
00:08:07,153 --> 00:08:09,030
Gosh. What a guy.

101
00:08:09,530 --> 00:08:10,531
Sir!

102
00:08:11,115 --> 00:08:13,826
The court called.
They need you right away.

103
00:08:15,578 --> 00:08:17,622
Abolish the Juvenile Act!

104
00:08:17,705 --> 00:08:19,707
-Abolish!
-Abolish!

105
00:08:19,790 --> 00:08:21,501
Abolish the Juvenile Act!

106
00:08:21,584 --> 00:08:23,294
-Abolish!
-Abolish!

107
00:08:23,377 --> 00:08:27,256
Enforce harsher punishment
for young violent offenders!

108
00:08:27,340 --> 00:08:28,299
-Enforce!
-Enforce!

109
00:08:28,382 --> 00:08:29,634
Yes, sir.

110
00:08:31,052 --> 00:08:32,053
Again?

111
00:08:33,221 --> 00:08:35,515
How bad is the injury?

112
00:08:36,891 --> 00:08:39,685
Yes, I understand.

113
00:08:39,769 --> 00:08:44,357
Yes, he should be treated first.
Let me know when it's over. Thank you.

114
00:08:44,941 --> 00:08:45,900
Okay.

115
00:08:45,983 --> 00:08:47,735
JUVENILE CRIMINAL COLLEGIATE DIVISION

116
00:08:50,488 --> 00:08:51,364
Excuse me.

117
00:08:52,657 --> 00:08:53,991
Who are you?

118
00:08:55,493 --> 00:08:57,787
Well, the thing is…

119
00:08:58,371 --> 00:09:00,998
This isn't a place
where people can just come and go.

120
00:09:01,582 --> 00:09:03,793
Who are you here to meet?

121
00:09:05,002 --> 00:09:08,422
-The new associate judge coming in today.
-Do you mean Judge Sim Eun-seok?

122
00:09:09,715 --> 00:09:10,841
Did you meet her?

123
00:09:11,884 --> 00:09:13,719
I heard she was running a little late

124
00:09:13,803 --> 00:09:15,888
because the transfer came out of the blue.

125
00:09:17,139 --> 00:09:19,141
Did you have an appointment with her?

126
00:09:19,225 --> 00:09:20,851
I don't need an appointment.

127
00:09:22,395 --> 00:09:23,437
I am…

128
00:09:25,273 --> 00:09:26,524
Sim Eun-seok.

129
00:09:28,776 --> 00:09:31,946
I'm your senior,
so I can talk casually, right?

130
00:09:39,078 --> 00:09:40,746
-Hey!
-My goodness.

131
00:09:40,830 --> 00:09:41,872
What's wrong with you?

132
00:09:42,456 --> 00:09:44,375
I told you not to call the TV station!

133
00:09:44,458 --> 00:09:48,296
Didn't I tell you you'll jinx everything
if you keep calling from the court?

134
00:09:49,046 --> 00:09:51,924
I'm walking on eggshells over there as is.

135
00:09:52,925 --> 00:09:56,470
Are you going to take responsibility
if I get fired?

136
00:09:56,554 --> 00:09:58,514
Mr. Kang. I told him to call you.

137
00:09:58,598 --> 00:10:00,057
We received an urgent case.

138
00:10:00,808 --> 00:10:01,684
What is it?

139
00:10:01,767 --> 00:10:04,687
The Yeonhwa Child Murder Case
has come to us.

140
00:10:05,271 --> 00:10:10,693
I'll tell the new associate judge
and Judge Tae-ju to gather in your room.

141
00:10:17,408 --> 00:10:18,534
JUVENILE PROTECTION CASE

142
00:10:29,045 --> 00:10:31,714
Sir, you have a meeting
with the press arbitration commission

143
00:10:31,797 --> 00:10:34,133
after this meeting.
What would you like to do for lunch?

144
00:10:43,059 --> 00:10:46,354
You know about
the Yeonhwa Child Murder Case, right?

145
00:10:48,689 --> 00:10:49,815
YEONHWA DISTRICT COURT

146
00:10:49,899 --> 00:10:52,401
Ji-hu!

147
00:10:52,985 --> 00:10:55,071
Ji-hu!

148
00:10:59,283 --> 00:11:01,744
Ji-hu!

149
00:11:04,413 --> 00:11:07,416
Ji-hu borrowed a phone from some older kid

150
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:10,294
because he needed to call his mom.

151
00:11:10,378 --> 00:11:12,463
But the guy said he needed

152
00:11:12,546 --> 00:11:14,674
to go home to charge it,

153
00:11:14,757 --> 00:11:17,134
so Ji-hu followed him there.

154
00:11:23,891 --> 00:11:26,811
The culprit is a 13-year-old minor

155
00:11:26,894 --> 00:11:29,689
who lives in the same apartment complex
as the victim.

156
00:11:30,356 --> 00:11:32,525
He has a small frame
with a height around 160 cm,

157
00:11:32,608 --> 00:11:35,403
but he managed to strangle
the eight-year-old to death,

158
00:11:36,153 --> 00:11:40,324
mutilated the body with a hatchet,
and disposed of the body.

159
00:11:40,408 --> 00:11:44,245
He disposed some of the organs
and body parts in the food waste bin,

160
00:11:44,328 --> 00:11:47,373
so they had to hold the funeral
without the body.

161
00:11:52,503 --> 00:11:55,256
He had no resentment
and didn't even know the victim.

162
00:11:55,840 --> 00:11:57,425
It happened in broad daylight

163
00:11:57,508 --> 00:12:00,803
at an apartment complex near
a police station and an elementary school.

164
00:12:02,722 --> 00:12:07,893
This is what juvenile crimes
are like these days.

165
00:12:10,646 --> 00:12:15,025
Kidnapping, murder,
body mutilation, and disposal.

166
00:12:15,651 --> 00:12:18,696
But the culprit is a young offender.

167
00:12:19,447 --> 00:12:23,409
Even the maximum 20-year sentence
would cause an uproar.

168
00:12:23,492 --> 00:12:26,829
Yet we can only sentence him
to two years in a juvenile reformatory

169
00:12:28,330 --> 00:12:30,916
all because he's under the age of 14.

170
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:32,668
NAME: BAEK SEONG-U
13 YEARS OLD

171
00:12:32,752 --> 00:12:35,379
We're definitely going to come under fire.

172
00:12:42,094 --> 00:12:43,888
I've heard about you
since you were a trainee.

173
00:12:44,722 --> 00:12:48,893
You surpassed all your male classmates
and entered the Central District Court.

174
00:12:49,435 --> 00:12:51,854
And you even went overseas
for further training on top of that.

175
00:12:52,354 --> 00:12:54,148
Seems like you're one of the elites.

176
00:12:54,648 --> 00:12:57,109
Good luck on this case

177
00:12:58,027 --> 00:12:59,862
since you were assigned as the judge.

178
00:13:01,280 --> 00:13:02,156
Yes, sir.

179
00:13:06,410 --> 00:13:09,455
The result may have already been decided,

180
00:13:09,955 --> 00:13:13,209
but all eyes will be on us.

181
00:13:15,211 --> 00:13:16,462
We have to be careful.

182
00:13:20,633 --> 00:13:24,762
As you may have noticed,
things are different here

183
00:13:24,845 --> 00:13:27,807
than they were
at the juvenile court you're from.

184
00:13:28,390 --> 00:13:31,644
You were only in charge
of juvenile protection cases, right?

185
00:13:31,727 --> 00:13:33,729
Here, at the Juvenile Criminal
Collegiate Division,

186
00:13:33,813 --> 00:13:37,650
we do juvenile protection cases
as well as juvenile criminal cases.

187
00:13:37,733 --> 00:13:41,570
The associate judge must read
about 80 cases per week,

188
00:13:41,654 --> 00:13:44,949
so that's about 300 cases a month,
give or take.

189
00:13:47,243 --> 00:13:49,912
Juvenile criminal cases
go through the collegial court

190
00:13:49,995 --> 00:13:52,122
and the rulings are delivered to Mr. Kang.

191
00:13:52,206 --> 00:13:55,668
Protection cases are done individually
according to the day of the week.

192
00:13:55,751 --> 00:13:57,837
There are more unsolved cases
than I thought.

193
00:13:59,171 --> 00:14:01,131
And here's the data you asked for.

194
00:14:03,926 --> 00:14:06,804
And I'm sorry about earlier.

195
00:14:07,388 --> 00:14:08,973
When I heard your name,

196
00:14:09,765 --> 00:14:11,725
I was expecting a male judge.

197
00:14:11,809 --> 00:14:14,478
Are you sure you're not disappointed
because I'm not a man?

198
00:14:15,896 --> 00:14:16,730
Pardon?

199
00:14:16,814 --> 00:14:19,149
Of course not.

200
00:14:20,526 --> 00:14:21,360
Yes?

201
00:14:28,784 --> 00:14:30,077
Nice to meet you.

202
00:14:30,160 --> 00:14:32,746
I'm Joo Yeong-sil, a judicial mediator.

203
00:14:32,830 --> 00:14:35,666
I'm Seo Beom, the assisting officer.

204
00:14:35,749 --> 00:14:37,084
Okay.

205
00:14:44,592 --> 00:14:46,677
Is this all
for the Yeonhwa Child Murder case?

206
00:14:46,760 --> 00:14:48,554
Yes, it's quite a lot.

207
00:14:48,637 --> 00:14:51,181
-The culprit's name's Baek Seong-u, right?
-Yes.

208
00:14:51,265 --> 00:14:53,934
Let's book a date for the trial
as soon as possible.

209
00:14:54,018 --> 00:14:57,146
It's not an ordinary case,
so contact the victim's family.

210
00:14:57,229 --> 00:14:58,522
Yes, ma'am.

211
00:15:00,983 --> 00:15:03,068
It's almost MJ time.

212
00:15:03,152 --> 00:15:05,863
Mr. Kang won't be joining us
since he has other plans.

213
00:15:07,573 --> 00:15:10,200
It's a tradition at our courthouse.

214
00:15:10,284 --> 00:15:12,119
It's short for, "meal with the judges."

215
00:15:12,703 --> 00:15:16,040
The kids who have been released,
the judge in charge,

216
00:15:16,123 --> 00:15:18,709
and the staff all gather
to have lunch together.

217
00:15:18,792 --> 00:15:21,503
We have a meal with the kids
and listen to their problems.

218
00:15:21,587 --> 00:15:23,380
It has quite a positive effect on them.

219
00:15:23,464 --> 00:15:25,090
Okay. Go ahead.

220
00:15:25,925 --> 00:15:28,260
You have to come too.

221
00:15:28,344 --> 00:15:30,554
The lunch will be meaningless

222
00:15:30,638 --> 00:15:32,056
if you and Mr. Kang aren't there.

223
00:15:32,139 --> 00:15:34,808
It's not like I sentenced the kids.

224
00:15:35,809 --> 00:15:38,062
Caring for the kids after their release

225
00:15:38,145 --> 00:15:40,481
is also one of the duties
of a Juvenile Court judge.

226
00:15:44,443 --> 00:15:47,780
You may not have judged their trials,
but they're still your responsibility.

227
00:15:48,447 --> 00:15:49,823
They'll be looking forward to it.

228
00:15:56,830 --> 00:15:58,123
Do I have to go?

229
00:15:59,917 --> 00:16:02,378
Are you giving up
on taekwondo for good, Do-seok?

230
00:16:02,878 --> 00:16:03,879
Yes.

231
00:16:04,546 --> 00:16:07,675
But I'm still looking
into becoming a security guard.

232
00:16:07,758 --> 00:16:10,844
I already got a license
and passed the GED at the facility.

233
00:16:10,928 --> 00:16:13,305
-I'm proud of you.
-Thank you.

234
00:16:14,682 --> 00:16:17,017
Yu-ri. How's your grandmother?

235
00:16:18,227 --> 00:16:20,104
She's doing a lot better.

236
00:16:20,187 --> 00:16:24,358
I'm getting my paycheck soon.

237
00:16:24,441 --> 00:16:28,070
I'll pay you back for the medicine
you bought for my grandma.

238
00:16:30,364 --> 00:16:32,574
I heard you're going
to start training soon.

239
00:16:32,658 --> 00:16:34,201
You don't need to pay me back.

240
00:16:34,284 --> 00:16:36,036
Just give me a haircut someday.

241
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:37,162
Me?

242
00:16:37,246 --> 00:16:39,415
Make me look like BTS.
You can do it, right?

243
00:16:39,498 --> 00:16:41,291
I need to know how good you are, right?

244
00:16:43,293 --> 00:16:46,672
You know, the director at the facility
has been complimenting you,

245
00:16:46,755 --> 00:16:48,173
saying you turned over a new leaf.

246
00:16:49,383 --> 00:16:52,594
Since you're now officially released,
how about we have a toast?

247
00:16:52,678 --> 00:16:53,512
Okay.

248
00:16:53,595 --> 00:16:54,471
Congratulations.

249
00:16:54,555 --> 00:16:55,973
-Congratulations.
-Thank you.

250
00:16:57,808 --> 00:17:00,019
-I have to use the restroom.
-Sure.

251
00:17:02,521 --> 00:17:04,314
He really adores them, doesn't he?

252
00:17:04,815 --> 00:17:08,193
I think the kids know that.
They are very fond of him as well.

253
